:: HousingOptions
/*Housing options - various affordability levels*/
<<set $step = 0>>
<<ShowInfo>>

<h3>Available Housing Options</h3>

<div class="housing-intro">
<p>You have $<<= $money>> in your bank account, but the minimum you should be spending for a livable apartment is $1100. You know that there is access to significantly more non-legal employment opportunities in other areas if you are willing to spend more on rent, closer to $1600.</p>
</div>

<hr>

Select an apartment to apply:

<hr>

<div class="housing-option">
<h4>Affordable Apartment</h4>
<p>A basic studio or 1-bedroom in a working-class neighborhood. Older building, but livable. Public transit accessible.</p>
<p><strong>Application Fee:</strong> $30</p>
<p><strong>Monthly Rent:</strong> $900</p>
<p><em>Landlords typically require income of 3x rent ($2,700/month)</em></p>

<<if $money >= 30>>
    <<link "Apply for Affordable Apartment">>
        <<set $selectedHousingType = "Affordable">>
        <<set $selectedApplicationFee = 30>>
        <<set $selectedMonthlyCost = 900>>
        <<goto "HousingApply">>
    <</link>>
<<else>>
    <p style="color: red;">You don't have enough money for this application fee.</p>
<</if>>
</div>

<hr>

<div class="housing-option">
<h4>Standard Apartment</h4>
<p>A decent 1-bedroom in a mixed neighborhood. Better maintained building with some amenities. You know this area has more employment opportunities.</p>
<p><strong>Application Fee:</strong> $50</p>
<p><strong>Monthly Rent:</strong> $1,400</p>
<p><em>Landlords typically require income of 3x rent ($4,200/month) and will scrutinize your documentation more carefully.</em></p>

<<if $money >= 50>>
    <<link "Apply for Standard Apartment">>
        <<set $selectedHousingType = "Standard">>
        <<set $selectedApplicationFee = 50>>
        <<set $selectedMonthlyCost = 1400>>
        <<goto "HousingApply">>
    <</link>>
<<else>>
    <p style="color: red;">You don't have enough money for this application fee.</p>
<</if>>
</div>

<hr>

<div class="housing-option">
<h4>Premium Apartment in Better Area</h4>
<p>A modern 1-2 bedroom in a nicer neighborhood with significantly more employment opportunitiesâ€”both legal and under-the-table work. However, the property owner may ask for and expect certain legal documents. The apartment search will be longer and you will have to balance it with the 10-12 hour days you've been working just to keep up with your family's needs.</p>
<p><strong>Application Fee:</strong> $75</p>
<p><strong>Monthly Rent:</strong> $1,800</p>
<p><em>Landlords require income of 3x rent ($5,400/month), full credit check, employment verification, and often a co-signer.</em></p>

<<if $money >= 75>>
    <<link "Apply for Premium Apartment">>
        <<set $selectedHousingType = "Premium">>
        <<set $selectedApplicationFee = 75>>
        <<set $selectedMonthlyCost = 1800>>
        <<goto "PremiumHousingConsequences">>
    <</link>>
<<else>>
    <p style="color: red;">You don't have enough money for this application fee.</p>
<</if>>
</div>

<hr>

<<link "Go back">> <<goto "HousingStart">> <</link>>
